  "text": "The work of Vershik-Kerov and Logan-Shepp only determines the asymptotic behavior of the expectation of is n (w). What about stronger results? A major breakthrough was made by Jinho Baik, Percy Deift, and Kurt Johansson [CITATION_1] , and has inspired much further work. To describe their results, let Ai(x) denote the Airy function, viz., the unique solution to the second-order differential equation",
